{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"370301fc-22fe-405a-918a-4c62b9c8566b","content":"In .NET MAUI, `OnStart`, `OnSleep`, and `OnResume` **still exist** on the `Application` class and work the same way. However, the recommended MAUI approach is to use **`Window` lifecycle events** instead:\n\nOverride `CreateWindow` in your `App` class:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created += (s, e) => { /* replaces OnStart */ };\n    window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* replaces OnSleep */ };\n    window.Resumed += (s, e) => { /* replaces OnResume */ };\n    window.Destroying += (s, e) => { /* cleanup */ };\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n- `Window` events are per-window (MAUI supports multi-window on iPad/desktop)\n- `Application.OnStart`/`OnSleep`/`OnResume` are app-wide and still work if you prefer the simpler approach\n- For **platform-specific** lifecycle hooks, use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7ea1c689-303b-44ec-b675-93e9774cf9b9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating lifecycle methods from Xamarin.Forms to .NET MAUI. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.\n\nIn Xamarin.Forms, you'd override `OnStart()`, `OnSleep()`, and `OnResume()` in your `Application` subclass.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the equivalent is to use the `Window` lifecycle events or the `ILifecycleBuilder` in `MauiProgram.cs`. Specifically:\n\n- The `Application` class still exists and you can still override `OnStart()`, but the recommended approach is to use `Window` lifecycle events.\n\n\n- You can override `CreateWindow()` in your `Application` class and subscribe to window events, or configure lifecycle events through `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` for platform-specific handling.\n- The `Application` class still supports `OnStart`, `OnSleep`, and `OnResume`, but the more idiomatic MAUI approach uses `Window` lifecycle events like `Created`, `Stopped`, `Resumed`, and `Destroying`.","outputTokens":579},"id":"66354f70-6ac1-45b0-813c-7cdf93adaab2","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:47:07.431Z","parentId":"438b4994-0b05-43ef-b2cf-d55f01029c5f"}
